---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ASTR | Gary McKeever" description="ASTR Unity project overview and playable WebGL build.">
  <section>
    <h1>ASTR</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      ASTR is where I test how rules, constraints, and progression systems behave when people can actually interact with them.
    </p>
    <div class="chips">
      <span class="chip">Unity</span>
      <span class="chip">C#</span>
      <span class="chip">WebGL</span>
      <span class="chip">Systems design experimentation</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Project Notes</h2>
    <p class="lead muted">
      I use this project to pressure-test system behavior in a smaller environment: resource limits, progression loops, and the tradeoffs that appear once a design has to run instead of just sound good on paper.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Playable Build</h2>
    <div class="unity-shell">
      <div id="gameContainer"></div>
    </div>
    <p class="project-meta">If loading takes time, keep this tab active while WebGL assets initialize.</p>
  </section>

  <script is:inline src="/TemplateData/UnityProgress.js"></script>
  <script is:inline src="/Build/UnityLoader.js"></script>
  <script is:inline>
    const container = document.getElementById('gameContainer');
    if (container && window.UnityLoader) {
      window.UnityLoader.instantiate('gameContainer', '/Build/build.json', {
        onProgress: window.UnityProgress
      });
    }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
